org.apache.avro

Interface LogicalTypes.LogicalTypeFactory

  • Enclosing class:
    LogicalTypes

    public static interface LogicalTypes.LogicalTypeFactory
    Factory interface and SPI for logical types. A LogicalTypeFactory can be registered in two ways:
    1. Manually, via LogicalTypes.register(LogicalTypeFactory) or LogicalTypes.register(String, LogicalTypeFactory)
    2. Automatically, when the LogicalTypeFactory implementation is a public class with a public no-arg constructor, is named in a file called /META-INF/services/org.apache.avro.LogicalTypes$LogicalTypeFactory, and both are available in the classpath
    See Also:
    ServiceLoader
